Ken Chenault, Chairman and CEO of American Express and a member of the President's Council on Jobs and Competitiveness, expressed his support for the American Jobs Act. He emphasized that creating more jobs is the most significant challenge facing America today. Chenault stated that he and his colleagues on the Jobs Council have been working to identify initiatives that can accelerate job creation and strengthen the economy. He appreciated the President's focus on this issue and noted that some of the Council's work, such as training and support for small businesses, is reflected in the President's recommendations. Chenault emphasized the need for sustained bipartisan action and expressed his willingness to work with the President and congressional leaders to create more jobs.